We typically use the boolean threw pattern instead of using a broad catch like this. The purpose is to still try to clean up even if the problem wasn't an Exception (like AssertionError):
boolean threw = true;
try {
  RewriteFiles = table.newRewrite().rewriteFiles(...).commit()
  threw = false;
} finally {
  if (threw) {
    Tasks.foreach(...)
        .run(fileIO::deleteFile);
  }
}

